description: This header file defines external API functions for the Daemon Engine UDP Object in the Advanced Networking Service Container (ANSC) framework. It includes function prototypes for creating, removing, enrolling objects, and initializing the daemon engine UDP component.

methods.name: AnscCreateDaemonEngineUdp
methods.description: Creates an instance of the Daemon Engine UDP object using provided context handles.

methods.name: AnscDeuoCreate
methods.description: Creates the Daemon Engine UDP object with specified container, owner, and reserved contexts.

methods.name: AnscDeuoRemove
methods.description: Removes and cleans up the Daemon Engine UDP object.

methods.name: AnscDeuoEnrollObjects
methods.description: Enrolls necessary objects into the Daemon Engine UDP object.

methods.name: AnscDeuoInitialize
methods.description: Initializes the Daemon Engine UDP object.
